        "def load_audio(file_path):\n",
        "    rate, data = wavfile.read(file_path)\n",
        "    if data.dtype == np.int16:\n",
        "        data = data / 32768.0  # Normalize to the range [-1.0, 1.0]\n",
        "    return data, rate\n",
        "file_path = '//content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav'\n",
        "audio, sample_rate = load_audio(file_path)\n",
        "print(\"Sample Rate:\", sample_rate)\n",
        "print(\"Audio Data Shape:\", audio.shape)\n"
      ]

            "\u001b[0;31mNameError\u001b[0m: name 'audio' is not defined"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio, sample_rate):\n",
        "    win_s = 4096  # Window size\n",
        "    hop_s = 512   # Hop size\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Create aubio pitch object\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", win_s, hop_s, sample_rate)\n",
        "    pitch_o.set_unit(\"Hz\")  # Set unit to Hertz\n",
        "    pitch_o.set_tolerance(0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Create a numpy array from the audio data\n",
        "    samples = np.array(audio, dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Initialize variables\n",
        "    pitch_values = []  # List to store pitch values\n",
        "    total_frames = len(samples)\n",
        "    frames_read = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Process audio in chunks\n",
        "    while frames_read < total_frames:\n",
        "        # Get current frame from the audio\n",
        "        current_frame = samples[frames_read:frames_read + win_s]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Ensure the current frame is one-dimensional and matches the expected size\n",
        "        current_frame_flat = np.ravel(current_frame)[:hop_s]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Compute pitch\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(current_frame_flat)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Add pitch value to the list\n",
        "        pitch_values.append(pitch)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Move to the next frame\n",
        "        frames_read += hop_s\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitch_values\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example usage:\n",
        "# Assuming you have 'audio' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio, sample_rate)\n",
        "print(pitch_values_hz)\n"
      ]
    },
    {

      "execution_count": null,

      },
      "outputs": [],

        "def load_audio(file_path):\n",
        "    print(\"Loading audio file:\", file_path)\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        rate, data = wavfile.read(file_path)\n",
        "        if data.dtype == np.int16:\n",
        "            data = data / 32768.0  # Normalize to the range [-1.0, 1.0]\n",
        "        return data, rate\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(\"Error loading audio:\", e)\n",
        "        return None, None\n"
      ]

        "def send_sos_message():\n",
        "    # Include the code to send an SOS message here\n",
        "    print(\"SOS message sent!\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Loop for pitch detection\n",
        "for audio_data, sample_rate in [audio_generator]:\n",
        "    # Process your audio data here\n",
        "    print(f\"Received batch with shape {audio_data.shape} and sample rate {sample_rate}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Detect pitches\n",
        "    pitches = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "    print(f\"Pitches: {pitches}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Check if pitch crosses 100 Hz\n",
        "    if any(pitch > 100 for pitch in pitches):\n",
        "        print(\"Pitch crossed 100 Hz threshold. Sending SOS message...\")\n",
        "        send_sos_message()\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "A3CWX6qyA-Ay"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import aubio\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i+hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n"
      ]
    },
    {

      "execution_count": null,

      "source": [
        "import aubio\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import librosa\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Check if audio data is not empty\n",
        "    if len(mono_audio_data) > 0:\n",
        "        # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "        padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "        audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Iterate over frames\n",
        "        for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "            frame = audio_data_padded[i:i+hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "            pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "            if pitch > 0:\n",
        "                pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "def load_audio(file_path, batch_size=512):\n",
        "    offset = 0\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        samples, sample_rate = librosa.load(file_path, sr=None, offset=offset, duration=batch_size, mono=False)\n",
        "        if len(samples) == 0:\n",
        "            break\n",
        "        offset += batch_size\n",
        "        yield samples, sample_rate\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example usage\n",
        "file_path = \"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\"\n",
        "audio_generator = load_audio(file_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "for audio_data, sample_rate in audio_generator:\n",
        "    print(f\"Received batch with shape {audio_data.shape} and sample rate {sample_rate}\")\n",
        "    pitches = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "    print(f\"Pitches: {pitches}\")\n"
      ]
    },

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "from twilio.rest import Client\n",
        "\n",
        "# Twilio credentials\n",
        "account_sid = 'ACe3cff7ef019e4609771082d571004ad9'\n",
        "auth_token = '1d6b910121a2c48d7cffe35428e657d7'\n",
        "client = Client(account_sid, auth_token)\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # Ensure audio_data is of type float32\n",
        "    audio_data = np.float32(audio_data)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", 2048, 1024, sample_rate)\n",
        "    pitch_o.set_unit(\"Hz\")\n",
        "    pitch_o.set_tolerance(0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "    for frame in audio_data.reshape(-1, 1024):\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "        pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "def load_audio(file_path, batch_size=1024):\n",
        "    audio_source = aubio.source(file_path)\n",
        "    sample_rate = audio_source.samplerate\n",
        "\n",
        "    offset = 0\n",
        "    audio_data = np.array([])\n",
        "\n",
        "    for samples, read in audio_source:\n",
        "        audio_data = np.concatenate([audio_data, samples])\n",
        "\n",
        "        offset += read\n",
        "\n",
        "        while len(audio_data) >= batch_size:\n",
        "            batch = audio_data[:batch_size]\n",
        "            audio_data = audio_data[batch_size:]\n",
        "            yield batch, sample_rate\n",
        "\n",
        "    if len(audio_data) > 0:\n",
        "        yield audio_data, sample_rate\n",
        "\n",
        "def send_location_message(location):\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        message = client.messages.create(\n",
        "            body=f'SOS: HELP! Location: {location}',\n",
        "            from_='+19789653881',\n",
        "            to='+916303814974'\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"Message sent with SID: {message.sid}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error sending SOS message: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Main script\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    file_path = \"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\"  # Replace with the actual path\n",
        "    audio_generator = load_audio(file_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for audio_data, sample_rate in audio_generator:\n",
        "        print(f\"Received batch with shape {audio_data.shape} and sample rate {sample_rate}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        pitches = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "        print(f\"Pitches: {pitches}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        if any(pitch > 100 for pitch in pitches):\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import pydub\n",
        "import librosa\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the pre-trained machine learning model\n",
        "model = joblib.load('scream_detection_model.joblib')\n",
        "\n",
        "def preprocess_audio(audio_file):\n",
        "    sound = pydub.AudioSegment.from_file(audio_file)\n",
        "    samples = np.array(sound.get_array_of_samples())\n",
        "    samples = samples.astype(np.float32)\n",
        "    return librosa.feature.mfcc(samples, sr=sound.frame_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "def predict_scream(audio_features):\n",
        "    # Assume you have a pre-trained machine learning model for scream detection\n",
        "    prediction = model.predict(audio_features.reshape(1, -1))\n",
        "    return prediction[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_detection_alarm(audio_file):\n",
        "    audio_features = preprocess_audio(audio_file)\n",
        "    prediction = predict_scream(audio_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if prediction == 1:\n",
        "        print(\"Scream detected! Activate alarm.\")\n",
        "        # Add code here to activate your alarm (e.g., play a loud sound)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(\"No scream detected.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    audio_file_path = \"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\"\n",
        "    scream_detection_alarm(audio_file_path)\n"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import librosa\n",
        "import pyin\n",
        "import pygame\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_with_alarm(audio_file):\n",
        "    # Load audio file\n",
        "    y, sr = librosa.load(audio_file, sr=None)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Use YIN pitch detection algorithm\n",
        "    pitches, magnitudes = pyin.yin(y, fmin=librosa.note_to_hz('C2'), fmax=librosa.note_to_hz('C7'))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get the pitch with the maximum magnitude\n",
        "    if len(pitches) > 0:\n",
        "        max_pitch_index = np.argmax(magnitudes)\n",
        "        detected_pitch = pitches[max_pitch_index]\n",
        "        print(f\"Detected pitch: {detected_pitch} Hz\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Set a pitch threshold for scream detection (adjust as needed)\n",
        "        scream_threshold = 500  # Adjust this threshold based on your application\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Trigger alarm if the detected pitch is above the threshold\n",
        "        if detected_pitch > scream_threshold:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            activate_alarm()\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            print(\"No scream detected.\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(\"No pitch detected.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "def activate_alarm():\n",
        "    # Initialize Pygame mixer\n",
        "    pygame.mixer.init()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Load and play a simple alarm sound (replace with your sound file)\n",
        "    pygame.mixer.music.load(\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\")\n",
        "    pygame.mixer.music.play()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Allow the alarm to play for a few seconds\n",
        "    pygame.time.delay(5000)  # 5000 milliseconds (5 seconds)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Stop the alarm\n",
        "    pygame.mixer.music.stop()\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    audio_file_path = \"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\"\n",
        "    pitch_detection_with_alarm(audio_file_path)\n"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import time\n",
        "import pygame # For Windows systems; you can use other methods for different platforms\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "THRESHOLD_PITCH = 200  # Adjust this threshold based on your environment\n",
        "ALARM_INTERVAL = 5  # Adjust the interval between alarms in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to indicate scream detection\n",
        "scream_detected = False\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i+hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_alarm():\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        global scream_detected\n",
        "        if scream_detected:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            pygame.mixer.init()\n",
        "            pygame.mixer.music.load(\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\")  # Replace with the path to your sound file\n",
        "            pygame.mixer.music.play()\n",
        "            time.sleep(ALARM_INTERVAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    # Assuming you have 'audio' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "    pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pitch in pitch_values_hz:\n",
        "        if pitch > THRESHOLD_PITCH:\n",
        "            scream_detected = True\n",
        "\n",
        "    alarm_thread = threading.Thread(target=scream_alarm)\n",
        "    alarm_thread.start()\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    main()\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "qviAQGJoxz1R",
        "outputId": "2a66cc0c-3194-4dda-d386-ac678ce97414"
      },

          "output_type": "stream",

            "    self.run()\n",
            "  File \"/usr/lib/python3.10/threading.py\", line 953, in run\n",
            "    self._target(*self._args, **self._kwargs)\n",
            "  File \"<ipython-input-32-8d974913ce83>\", line 49, in scream_alarm\n",
            "pygame.error: ALSA: Couldn't open audio device: No such file or directory\n"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import time\n",
        "import IPython.display as ipd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "THRESHOLD_PITCH = 200  # Adjust this threshold based on your environment\n",
        "ALARM_INTERVAL = 5  # Adjust the interval between alarms in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to indicate scream detection\n",
        "scream_detected = False\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # ... (same as your existing code)\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i+hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_alarm():\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        if scream_detected:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            ipd.Audio(\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\")  # Replace with the path to your sound file\n",
        "            time.sleep(ALARM_INTERVAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    # Assuming you have 'audio' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "    pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pitch in pitch_values_hz:\n",
        "        if pitch > THRESHOLD_PITCH:\n",
        "            scream_detected = True\n",
        "\n",
        "    alarm_thread = threading.Thread(target=scream_alarm)\n",
        "    alarm_thread.start()\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    main()\n"

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import time\n",
        "from pydub import AudioSegment\n",
        "from pydub.playback import play\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "THRESHOLD_PITCH = 200  # Adjust this threshold based on your environment\n",
        "ALARM_INTERVAL = 5  # Adjust the interval between alarms in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to indicate scream detection\n",
        "scream_detected = False\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # ... (same as your existing code)\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "  # ...\n",
        "# Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "# ...\n",
        "# Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "hop_size = 1024   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # ... (same as your existing code)\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 1024   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    if len(audio_data.shape) > 1 and audio_data.shape[1] == 2:\n",
        "        mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=1)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        mono_audio_data = audio_data\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i + hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_alarm():\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        if scream_detected:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            alarm_sound = AudioSegment.from_file(\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\")\n",
        "            play(alarm_sound)\n",
        "            time.sleep(ALARM_INTERVAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    # Assuming you have 'audio' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "    pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pitch in pitch_values_hz:\n",
        "        if pitch > THRESHOLD_PITCH:\n",
        "            scream_detected = True\n",

        "    alarm_thread.start()\n",

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import time\n",
        "from pydub import AudioSegment\n",
        "from pydub.playback import play\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "THRESHOLD_PITCH = 200  # Adjust this threshold based on your environment\n",
        "ALARM_INTERVAL = 5  # Adjust the interval between alarms in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to indicate scream detection\n",
        "scream_detected = False\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # ... (same as your existing code)\n",
        "    # Initialize YIN pitch detection\n",
        "    hop_size = 1024   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    if len(audio_data.shape) > 1 and audio_data.shape[1] == 2:\n",
        "        mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=1)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        mono_audio_data = audio_data\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i + hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "from IPython.display import display, Audio\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_alarm():\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        if scream_detected:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            alarm_sound = Audio(\"/content/alarm-110066.mp3\", autoplay=True)\n",
        "            display(alarm_sound)\n",
        "            time.sleep(ALARM_INTERVAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    # Assuming you have 'audio' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "    pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "    alarm_sound = None  # Initialize the variable\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pitch in pitch_values_hz:\n",
        "        if pitch > THRESHOLD_PITCH:\n",
        "            scream_detected = True\n",
        "            alarm_sound = AudioSegment.from_file(\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\")  # Initialize alarm_sound\n",
        "\n",
        "    alarm_thread = threading.Thread(target=scream_alarm)\n",
        "    alarm_thread.start()\n",
        "\n",
        "    if scream_detected and alarm_sound:\n",
        "        play(alarm_sound)  # Play the alarm sound when scream is detected\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    main()\n"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [],

        "id": "E8tUfowwJbm9"

      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import aubio\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import time\n",
        "from IPython.display import Audio, display\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "THRESHOLD_PITCH = 200  # Adjust this threshold based on your environment\n",
        "ALARM_INTERVAL = 5  # Adjust the interval between alarms in seconds\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to indicate scream detection\n",
        "scream_detected = False\n",
        "\n",
        "def pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate):\n",
        "    # ... (same as your existing code)\n",
        "    hop_size = 512   # Hop size (frame shift) for pitch detection\n",
        "    pitch_o = aubio.pitch(\"yin\", hop_size=hop_size, samplerate=sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pitches = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Convert stereo to mono\n",
        "    mono_audio_data = np.mean(audio_data, axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Pad the audio data to ensure the last frame has the correct size\n",
        "    padding = hop_size - (len(mono_audio_data) % hop_size)\n",
        "    audio_data_padded = np.pad(mono_audio_data, (0, padding), mode='constant')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Iterate over frames\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(audio_data_padded), hop_size):\n",
        "        frame = audio_data_padded[i:i+hop_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Perform pitch detection on the current frame\n",
        "        pitch = pitch_o(frame)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Check if pitch is valid\n",
        "        if pitch > 0:\n",
        "            pitches.append(pitch)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            pitches.append(0.0)  # Default value when pitch is not detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    return pitches\n",
        "\n",
        "def scream_alarm():\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        if scream_detected:\n",
        "            print(\"Scream detected! Activating alarm.\")\n",
        "            display(Audio(filename=\"/content/408607__miguelab1998__33-girl-scream.wav\", autoplay=True))  # Replace with the path to your sound file\n",
        "            time.sleep(ALARM_INTERVAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    # Assuming you have 'audio_data' and 'sample_rate' defined elsewhere\n",
        "    pitch_values_hz = pitch_detection_yin(audio_data, sample_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    global scream_detected\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pitch in pitch_values_hz:\n",
        "        if pitch > THRESHOLD_PITCH:\n",
        "            scream_detected = True\n",
